US ‘Loose Future’ tour is a WRAP. What a dream tour with a dream crew. We laughed, we cried, we drove through rain, sleet, and snow. Thank you for all the year end love for ‘Loose Future.’ As a thank you gift, here are some first ever voice memos from songs from the record. These were all recorded right after I first wrote the songs, and it’s wild to hear how much they have changed. 🫶 

I can usually remember the exact place I write all my songs, and these were recorded in Nashville, Nantucket, and Bisbee. Verrrry raw pieces from a place in time, outta tune guitars and all. Hehe. Also, a very clear indicator that I don’t stop writing lyrics for a song pretty much right up until I’m in the studio cutting it. ❤️cma

Happy holidays from Dreamy Draw. At the end of each year I climb one of these Arizona mountains solo. For reflection, for songs, for poems… a moment of resetting after a year of wandering and going and being with friends and loved ones. The stillness is jarring out here in the desert. You can hear the roadrunner dart across the dust. But, it’s necessary. People think the desert is mystic. That’s because it lets your subconscious speak. The truth is mystic. 

I hope you all find a quiet moment to hear what your hearts and minds have to say at the end of this year. With love ❤️ cma
Woah. Playing @carnegiehall next year with some gems. 🥲😍

It is complex— 
trying to sum up a year 
I lived with great sorrow 
And in brief moments, bursts of joy
My heart broke one million times over, 
—yet never beyond repair
There were many walks, long to heal, short to exercise, secrets kept, a flooded basement, a stolen backpack, a thousand kisses, an Italian dreamscape,  many partings, misunderstandings, desire, longing —always longing
A poet doesn’t go a year without longing
There was friendship, and its ever evolving form
There was music, harmonies, sometimes late into the night, and sometimes even better than sex
And when there was joy there was dancing with moves sporadic and wild
The were enough tears to fill a large wine glass, and enough failures to lower all expectations
Valleys can be wide 
There were motels and couches and big fancy beds in England, but the class only came in bursts, just like joy
I can try to explain, but you still won’t get the full scoop
You cannot sum up a year — especially one so transformative, a year of flames, waiting to rise a Phoenix, and all the substantial years to follow with all their little sorrows and joys.

2023. 💫🥲 
See ya on the road sometime this year.

Nashville’s Courtney Marie Andrews has spent the last decade touring and honing her folk sound, but it may have taken a global pandemic to allow the Grammy-nominated singer-songwriter the time to master her artistry, both on and off the stage. During this forced time of “rest,” Andrews published her first book of poetry, publicly showcased her paintings for the first time, and wrote a collection of jaw-dropping songs that would become her latest record 𝙇𝙤𝙤𝙨𝙚 𝙁𝙪𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙚. Produced by Sam Evian, Andrews’ loving lyrics are supported by an all-star cast of musicians like Chris Bear of Grizzly Bear, Josh Kaufman and Sam Owens. The result might be Andrews’ finest work yet, pushing her to sonic depths beyond the obvious Americana sound.

Watch @CourtneyMarieAndrews perform live at WNXP’s Sonic Cathedral 👉 link in bio. 

Cover photo: @prestonrevans

‘Standing in the Rain’ 
🫀🫀🫀🫀🫀🫀 
Old/new to you song.

My almost annual pilgrimage to Long Point Lighthouse in the inimitable P-town. A lighthouse is a metaphor for so many things: guidance, hope, mystery, solitude. It’s a long jetty walk to get here, but the journey is worth it because I re-learn year after year; about not only my own imperfections and complexities but the willingness to walk towards learning from them next time around.

In your darkest hour, may you find the light that guides you safely into the harbor. 

2023/2021/2019

Happy 3rd birthday to Old Flowers🥹

Gathering the memories from making this record, I’m remembering how it truly felt like my first fully self-realized piece of art. During the record I lived in an almost French alps style cottage in the hills of Beachwood Canyon. I didn’t go out much— just walked in the canyon and recorded— a deep time of self-reflection and putting my heart back together. This record feels like the time of my life when I became a woman. 

@sarloson inspired honest and creative takes from me and @twainband was a huge part of this record, and I owe so much of the magic to him. @james_krivchenia brought so much magic, too. 

I won’t ever forget recording ‘Guilty’ lying on the floor late at night under Mat’s piano, or only recording one version of ‘Carnival Dream’ because I got it on the first take, or running around like crazy people to create little spell breakers in ‘Break the spell.’ A truly special time. 

Thank you to all who have listened over the years. All my love and gratitude to you. ❤️🥹

Happy one year to ‘Loose Future.’ 
I lived at @flyingcloudrecordings for an entire summer in 2021. I was Sam & Hannah’s “roomate.” Walked for hours every morning in the National park, recorded in the afternoons, swam in the river, cooked beautiful meals together, and explored sound in a profound and slow way. This record taught me the importance of patience and process, and that living alongside your art is important. 

I painted the cover in Bisbee, Arizona the following winter. While painting, my mentor stumbled upon me while hiking, and encouraged me to paint my own cover. 
The album and the painting are ultimately a testament to wanting to love, and being unable to authentically express it in its ever-changing landscapes despite our best efforts. 

Thank you to all who have listened. Loose Future. You truly can’t predict what is around the next bend. 🔮

I have the great honor of performing a @john_prine song tomorrow, October 10th, at the @theryman in John’s honor. 

It is still one of the great privilege’s of my lifetime to have gotten to sing with him in the year before his passing, and I feel incredibly lucky to get to perform in his name tomorrow night. 🥹 Talk about grace and authenticity. No one wrote ‘em like him and remained as humble and giving while doing so. @fprine @ohboyrecords ❤️

Happy New Year. 🥂 
I generally love this eve because it instills hope of new beginnings, promise, could be’s, what if’s, dreams both small, and big, kisses, dances, music, self-reflection, and everything I cherish about life all wrapped up into one night. I’m wearing my aunt’s old velvet dress and welcoming a New Year with very open arms. 🪄 Can’t wait to make more art! Write more songs & poems! Love harder! Learn from my mistakes!! Cry and laugh all the way into another year!
Oh, ya know, just holding the first pre-edited copy of book number two & some natural beauty that aided me to the finish line. 🥲
